# MVP Specification

## 1. Base Platform Requirements
- Active open source community
- Comprehensive documentation
- Flexible architecture
- Stable API
- Extensible plugin system

## 2. Core Features

### 2.1. Visual Builder Enhancement
- Extended drag-and-drop functionality
- Responsive components library
- State management system
- Reusable components support

### 2.2. Backend Capabilities
- Advanced API endpoint creation
- Automatic documentation generation
- Custom middleware support
- Flexible data modeling

### 2.3. AI Assistant Integration
#### Design Support
- Component generation
- UX/UI suggestions
- Layout optimization
- Real-time assistance

#### Backend Support
- API generation
- Database optimization
- Security suggestions
- Documentation help

## 3. Technical Requirements

### 3.1. Performance
- AI response time < 3s
- Smooth editor operation
- Optimal resource usage
- Maintained platform performance

### 3.2. Scalability
- Multi-user support
- Efficient caching
- Database optimization

### 3.3. Security
- Security audit system
- Generated code validation
- Data protection measures

## 4. Implementation Phases

### Phase 1 (1-2 months)
- Base platform selection and analysis
- Basic AI integration
- Proof of Concept development

### Phase 2 (2-3 months)
- Feature expansion
- Integration testing
- Documentation
- Beta testing

## 5. Success Criteria
- Functional AI assistant
- Stable platform integration
- Basic feature set working
- Documentation completed
- Initial user testing feedback
